The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Madurai, Dec. 31 (PTI): Former DMK law minister Aladi Aruna, 70, and his friend, were killed yesterday by assailants near Alangulam, about 150 km here.

 Gang members who came on three two-wheelers picked up a quarrel with Aruna 

and two persons with him before opening fire.

 Patna: Patna district magistrate Gautam Goswami, keen to work for a corporate house as its senior vice-president, sent his resignation to the state government on Friday, reports our special correspondent. Chief secretary K.A.H. Subramaniam confirmed that he has received a copy of Goswami?s resignation but said no decision has been taken. Goswami gave no reason for his resignation.

 New Delhi: The baton passed to Air Chief Marshal S.P. Tyagi as the chief of the air force on Friday, reports our special correspondent. Air Chief Marshal S. Krishnaswamy retired. The army also got a new vice-chief today in Lieutenant General B.S. Thakur. Air Chief Marshal Tyagi, 59, was commanding the Western Air Command before taking up the top job in the air force. Air Chief Marshal Tyagi is a veteran of the 1965 and 1971 wars with Pakistan.




